After each population was constructed, we took 1,000 samples of size 500, and for each of these 1,000 samples we constructed a confidence interval using both the naive method (i.e., ignoring the complex sample design and pretending to have a simple random sample) and the proposed bootstrap method. By seeing if each of these confidence intervals included the true population prevalence, we calculated \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
