Unfortunately, the term “design effect” has taken on two meanings in the sampling literature.12,18 The first meaning is the ratio of the variance of the estimate under a specified sampling plan to the variance under simple random sampling (deff). An alternative definition is based on the ratio of the standard errors (deft). Since\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
\usepackage{amsmath}
\usepackage{wasysym} 
\usepackage{amsfonts} 
\usepackage{amssymb} 
\usepackage{amsbsy}
\usepackage{mathrsfs}
\usepackage{upgreek}
\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
\begin{document}$${\sqrt {deff} }$$\end{document}=deft, readers who prefer deft can make the appropriate conversion.

